description: A visitor center is a building housing information for visitors, typically including some or all of the following: information resources, facilities (e.g. restrooms, drinking water), ranger staff, and exhibits.
howToMap: Add a visitor center by creating a point on top of the associated building and selecting "Visitor Center" from the "Select feature type" menu. Additionally, trace the building footprint if it has not been added already.

description: A trailhead is the point or area at which a trail begins.
howToMap: Add a trailhead by creating a point at the start of the trail and selecting "Trailhead" from the "Select feature type" menu.

description: An minor road is a minor public road, typically at the lowest level of the interconnecting network. It is of lower importance than a secondary road and is not a residential street. If a road's classification is unknown, default to the "Minor Road" preset.
howToMap: Add an unclassified road by tracing its centerline from beginning to end and selecting "Unclassified Road" from the "Select feature type" menu.

description: A residential road is a road accessing residential areas.
howToMap: Add a residential road by tracing its centerline from beginning to end and selecting "Residential Road" from the "Select feature type" menu.

description: A primary road is a major highway, normally with at least two lanes.
howToMap: Add a primary road by tracing its centerline from beginning to end and selecting "Primary Road" from the "Select feature type" menu.

description: A secondary road is a highway that is not part of a major route but forms a link in the national route network. It usually has two lanes, separated by a centerline.
howToMap: Add a secondary road by tracing its centerline from beginning to end and selecting "Secondary Road" from the "Select feature type" menu.

description: A service road is a road accessing a building, service station, beach, campsite, business park, parking lot, driveway, or other services.
howToMap: Add a service road by tracing its centerline from beginning to end and selecting "Service Road" from the "Select feature type" menu.
